HEADWORD: Hydrometeorology
<hw>Hy`dro*me`te*or*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>meteorology</ets>.]</ety> <def>That
branch of meteorology which relates to, or treats of, water in the
atmosphere, or its phenomena, as rain, clouds, snow, hail, storms,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

